<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-19-0396 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper concerns the design of the simplified Boiling Water Reactor[SBWR], which is an advanced light water reactor being developed by GeneralElectric of the U.S.A. together with other participants. The design usesnatural circulation to provide flow to the reactor core, and incorporatesbasic passive safety features which place little reliance on operatoractions in emergencies. The objectives of General Electric's SBWR programmeare described, together with a summary of the proposed design features,and an assessment of potential advantages. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>